						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Super-Hampster wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Also someone said that Windows XP runs ok on 128MB of RAM. Since when? It runs like crap on 256 and not too much better on 512. It runs OK on 768MB, but still kinda slow.</div>
<br />A few years back I found an old K6 that used to run Windows 98. I managed to upgrade it's RAM to 128MB and it worked very well with XP. I used it as an extra PC at my girlfriend's house, and it was enough for browsing the web with Firefox, editing all kinds of documents and running old games and emulating classic systems. That PC is retired again, as I bought a notebook and my in-laws got a new PC, but it was just fine last time I used it.
<br />
<br />Plus I've been using XP under a virtual machine with 384MB of RAM and I have no complaints. My real PC has 2GB and my notebook just 1GB.</div>

					
